verses.text_plain: The burden of Egypt. Behold, the Lord rideth upon a swift cloud, and shall come into Egypt: and the idols of Egypt shall be moved at his presence, and the heart of Egypt shall melt in the midst of it.
verses.verse_html: 1The burden of Egypt. Behold, the Lord rideth upon a swift cloud, and shall come into Egypt: and the idols of Egypt shall be moved at his presence, and the heart of Egypt shall melt in the midst of it.

verses.text_plain: And I will set the Egyptians against the Egyptians: and they shall fight every one against his brother, and every one against his neighbour; city against city, and kingdom against kingdom.
verses.verse_html:
2And I will set the Egyptians against the Egyptians: and they shall fight every one against his brother, and every one against his neighbour; city against city, and kingdom against kingdom. ▼
▼ set: Heb. mingle

verses.text_plain: And the spirit of Egypt shall fail in the midst thereof; and I will destroy the counsel thereof: and they shall seek to the idols, and to the charmers, and to them that have familiar spirits, and to the wizards.
verses.verse_html:
3And the spirit of Egypt shall fail in the midst thereof; and I will destroy the counsel thereof: and they shall seek to the idols, and to the charmers, and to them that have familiar spirits, and to the wizards. ▼
▼ fail: Heb. be emptied
 , ▼
▼ destroy: Heb. swallow up

tokens.text: and to them that have familiar spirits

footnotes.body_html: ▼ fail: Heb. be emptied
▼ destroy: Heb. swallow up

verses.text_plain: And the Egyptians will I give over into the hand of a cruel lord; and a fierce king shall rule over them, saith the Lord, the Lord of hosts.
verses.verse_html:
4And the Egyptians will I give over into the hand of a cruel lord; and a fierce king shall rule over them, saith the Lord, the Lord of hosts. ▼
▼ give…: or, shut up

footnotes.body_html: ▼ give…: or, shut up

verses.text_plain: And the waters shall fail from the sea, and the river shall be wasted and dried up.
verses.verse_html: 5And the waters shall fail from the sea, and the river shall be wasted and dried up.

verses.text_plain: And they shall turn the rivers far away; and the brooks of defence shall be emptied and dried up: the reeds and flags shall wither.
verses.verse_html: 6And they shall turn the rivers far away; and the brooks of defence shall be emptied and dried up: the reeds and flags shall wither.

verses.text_plain: The paper reeds by the brooks, by the mouth of the brooks, and every thing sown by the brooks, shall wither, be driven away, and be no more.
verses.verse_html:
7The paper reeds by the brooks, by the mouth of the brooks, and every thing sown by the brooks, shall wither, be driven away, and be no more. ▼
▼ and be…: Heb. and shall not be

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and be…: Heb. and shall not be
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and be…: Heb. and shall not be

verses.text_plain: The fishers also shall mourn, and all they that cast angle into the brooks shall lament, and they that spread nets upon the waters shall languish.
verses.verse_html: 8The fishers also shall mourn, and all they that cast angle into the brooks shall lament, and they that spread nets upon the waters shall languish.

verses.text_plain: Moreover they that work in fine flax, and they that weave networks, shall be confounded.
verses.verse_html:
9Moreover they that work in fine flax, and they that weave networks, shall be confounded. ▼
▼ networks: or, white works

footnotes.body_html: ▼ networks: or, white works

verses.text_plain: And they shall be broken in the purposes thereof, all that make sluices and ponds for fish.
verses.verse_html:
10And they shall be broken in the purposes thereof, all that make sluices and ponds for fish. ▼
▼ purposes: Heb. foundations
 , ▼
▼ for fish: Heb. of living things

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for fish: Heb. of living things
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for fish: Heb. of living things

verses.text_plain: Surely the princes of Zoan are fools, the counsel of the wise counsellors of Pharaoh is become brutish: how say ye unto Pharaoh, I am the son of the wise, the son of ancient kings?
verses.verse_html: 11Surely the princes of Zoan are fools, the counsel of the wise counsellors of Pharaoh is become brutish: how say ye unto Pharaoh, I am the son of the wise, the son of ancient kings?

verses.text_plain: Where are they? where are thy wise men? and let them tell thee now, and let them know what the Lord of hosts hath purposed upon Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 12Where are they? where are thy wise men? and let them tell thee now, and let them know what the Lord of hosts hath purposed upon Egypt.

tokens.text: thee now, and let them know

verses.text_plain: The princes of Zoan are become fools, the princes of Noph are deceived; they have also seduced Egypt, even they that are the stay of the tribes thereof.
verses.verse_html:
13The princes of Zoan are become fools, the princes of Noph are deceived; they have also seduced Egypt, even they that are the stay of the tribes thereof. ▼
▼ they that…: or, governors: Heb. corners

footnotes.body_text: ▼ they that…: or, governors: Heb. corners
footnotes.body_html: ▼ they that…: or, governors: Heb. corners

verses.text_plain: The Lord hath mingled a perverse spirit in the midst thereof: and they have caused Egypt to err in every work thereof, as a drunken man staggereth in his vomit.
verses.verse_html:
14The Lord hath mingled a perverse spirit in the midst thereof: and they have caused Egypt to err in every work thereof, as a drunken man staggereth in his vomit. ▼
▼ a perverse…: Heb. a spirit of perversities

tokens.text: thereof: and they have caused Egypt

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a perverse…: Heb. a spirit of perversities
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a perverse…: Heb. a spirit of perversities

verses.text_plain: Neither shall there be any work for Egypt, which the head or tail, branch or rush, may do.
verses.verse_html: 15Neither shall there be any work for Egypt, which the head or tail, branch or rush, may do.

verses.text_plain: In that day shall Egypt be like unto women: and it shall be afraid and fear because of the shaking of the hand of the Lord of hosts, which he shaketh over it.
verses.verse_html: 16In that day shall Egypt be like unto women: and it shall be afraid and fear because of the shaking of the hand of the Lord of hosts, which he shaketh over it.

verses.text_plain: And the land of Judah shall be a terror unto Egypt, every one that maketh mention thereof shall be afraid in himself, because of the counsel of the Lord of hosts, which he hath determined against it.
verses.verse_html: 17And the land of Judah shall be a terror unto Egypt, every one that maketh mention thereof shall be afraid in himself, because of the counsel of the Lord of hosts, which he hath determined against it.

verses.text_plain: In that day shall five cities in the land of Egypt speak the language of Canaan, and swear to the Lord of hosts; one shall be called, The city of destruction.
verses.verse_html:
18In that day shall five cities in the land of Egypt speak the language of Canaan, and swear to the Lord of hosts; one shall be called, The city of destruction. ▼
▼ the language: Heb. the lip
 , ▼
▼ of destruction: or, of Heres, or, of the sun

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the language: Heb. the lip

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of destruction: or, of Heres, or, of the sun
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of destruction: or, of Heres, or, of the sun

verses.text_plain: In that day shall there be an altar to the Lord in the midst of the land of Egypt, and a pillar at the border thereof to the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 19In that day shall there be an altar to the Lord in the midst of the land of Egypt, and a pillar at the border thereof to the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And it shall be for a sign and for a witness unto the Lord of hosts in the land of Egypt: for they shall cry unto the Lord because of the oppressors, and he shall send them a saviour, and a great one, and he shall deliver them.
verses.verse_html: 20And it shall be for a sign and for a witness unto the Lord of hosts in the land of Egypt: for they shall cry unto the Lord because of the oppressors, and he shall send them a saviour, and a great one, and he shall deliver them.

tokens.text: And it shall be for a sign

verses.text_plain: And the Lord shall be known to Egypt, and the Egyptians shall know the Lord in that day, and shall do sacrifice and oblation; yea, they shall vow a vow unto the Lord, and perform it.
verses.verse_html: 21And the Lord shall be known to Egypt, and the Egyptians shall know the Lord in that day, and shall do sacrifice and oblation; yea, they shall vow a vow unto the Lord, and perform it.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord shall smite Egypt: he shall smite and heal it: and they shall return even to the Lord, and he shall be intreated of them, and shall heal them.
verses.verse_html: 22And the Lord shall smite Egypt: he shall smite and heal it: and they shall return even to the Lord, and he shall be intreated of them, and shall heal them.

verses.text_plain: In that day shall there be a highway out of Egypt to Assyria, and the Assyrian shall come into Egypt, and the Egyptian into Assyria, and the Egyptians shall serve with the Assyrians.
verses.verse_html: 23In that day shall there be a highway out of Egypt to Assyria, and the Assyrian shall come into Egypt, and the Egyptian into Assyria, and the Egyptians shall serve with the Assyrians.

verses.text_plain: In that day shall Israel be the third with Egypt and with Assyria, even a blessing in the midst of the land:
verses.verse_html: 24In that day shall Israel be the third with Egypt and with Assyria, even a blessing in the midst of the land:

verses.text_plain: Whom the Lord of hosts shall bless, saying, Blessed be Egypt my people, and Assyria the work of my hands, and Israel mine inheritance.
verses.verse_html: 25Whom the Lord of hosts shall bless, saying, Blessed be Egypt my people, and Assyria the work of my hands, and Israel mine inheritance.
